  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "We sometimes use a [`verifyCallResult`](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/02fcc75bb7f35376c22def91b0fb9bc7a50b9458/contracts/utils/Address.sol#L201-L205) helper to rethrow the returndata if a low level call results in an error:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n        (bool success, bytes memory returndata) = target.call(data);\r\n        return verifyCallResult(success, returndata, errorMessage);\r\n```\r\n\r\nWith compiler optimizations turned on, if the returndata contains a custom error, Hardhat is not able to decode the rethrown custom error, presumably because it can't identify where the error actually originates because rethrowing is not the standard solc subroutine.\r\n\r\nThings work fine with optimizations turned off.",
